to the editor re cellphones and caller id are making it harder for pollsters to pick a winner news article nov 5 your article about the problems that political pollsters face getting accurate results left one important question unanswered why this is hardly a bad thing politicians who ca n't rely on polls will have to decide issues on their merits or vote their consciences candidates will have to state their opinions not what they think voters want to hear the media will have to cover the issues not which candidate is ahead at the moment we may all become more informed citizens hard to see a downside to any of that daniel kittay wynantskill ny nov 5 2002

